content:
The Event Monitoring Analytics App comes with a set of prebuilt dashboards so that you can start exploring your data right away. Data from your org is automatically loaded into your Event Monitoring Analytics App datasets when it’s generated.

Most of the dashboards represent a single event type on the EventLogFile object. The EventLogFile object reference contains detailed information about each event type. Let’s get a quick idea about what each dashboard does.

Analytics Adoption: CRM Analytics usage and performance.
Apex Executions: Apex code executions and performance.
API: API usage and performance, including object use, processing speed, and methods invoked.
Dashboards: Dashboard adoption and performance.
Files: Content transfers (downloads, uploads, or previews) and file adoption.
Lightning Adoption: User interactions with Lightning Experience on desktop and mobile devices.
Lightning Performance: Optimizing performance and user interactions with Lightning Experience and the Salesforce mobile app.
Login-As: Admins using login-as feature and on which user accounts.
My Trust: Overall idea of events taking place in your org, average speed of transactions, and correlated by User IDs.
Page Views (URIs): Pages users are accessing in the Salesforce desktop app.
Report Downloads: Users downloading reports and where they’re downloading them from.
Reports: Trends in reporting, users running specific reports, and performance issues.
RestAPI: REST API usage and endpoint traffic, including IP ranges and methods called.
Setup Audit Trail: Changes users making in Setup area.
User Logins: Login trends by user and access information.
Visualforce Requests: Trends in Visualforce adoption and page performance.
title: Event Monitoring Analytics App Prebuilt Dashboards
